               <p>FRANCIS NIXON. I am a <rs id="t18260622-88-viclabel427" type="occupation">solicitor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-88-victim577 t18260622-88-viclabel427"></join> - my chambers are in <placeName id="t18260622-88-crimeloc428">Field-court, Gray's Inn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-88-crimeloc428" type="placeName" value="Field-court, Gray's Inn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260622-88-crimeloc428" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260622-88-off425 t18260622-88-crimeloc428"></join>. On Monday, the 29th of May, I found an officer there, who said he had a boy in custody, on a charge of stealing a seal of mine. I went to Marlborough-street, and the prisoner was committed. I had left the seal on my desk on the Saturday before - he had been my errand-boy about three months, and had behave exceedingly well.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260622-88-person578">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HOWS BEARCROFT
               <interp inst="t18260622-88-person578" type="surname" value="HOWS BEARCROFT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260622-88-person578" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260622-88-person578" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. - The prisoner brought this seal to pawn for 3s. - I asked where he got it - he said it was his master's, Mr. Nixon. who kept a chandler's-shop, in Fullwood's-rents; he afterwards said it was Mr. Nixon's, of Field-court.</p>
